{
  "texts": [
    "Outputs like this help preoperative strategy and intraoperative real-life decisions through visualization of areas worthy of receiving immediate attention; on the other hand, the estimated probability will assist decision-making.",
    "Above all, classification results combined with other quantitative metrics like the confidence score provide extra quantitative information regarding the probability of malignancy that supports diagnosing a condition.",
    "For example, the very high Dice Coefficient of 0.96 indicates the accuracy at segmentation, while the high classification accuracy of 92.3% ensures critical lesion types are identified reliably.",
    "In addition, the outputs of such a network are quite easily integrated into diagnostic imaging platforms where clinicians can overlay colonoscopy images with results to enhance visualization.",
    "The framework limits diagnostic variability and provides actionable insight to enhance diagnostic accuracy and promote improved patient outcomes."
  ]
}